Hey, should we move this ```ParquetHdfsWriter``` also to the gobblin-parquet module? Similar, to what you suggested me in [PR#2101](https://github.com/apache/incubator-gobblin/pull/2101). It can be placed in the gobblin-parquet module within ```writer``` package. What do you think?
@tilakpatidar Yes. All specific constructs related to parquet should be moved to gobblin-parquet module.

@zxcware I have encountered an issue while writing JSON dumps to parquet using JsonIntermediateToParquetGroupConverter and the builder class ParquetDataWriterBuilder. The conversion from JSON to parquet was successful. Writing to parquet format using our builder class is failing. In tests, we are able to write parquet records but it fails in Gobblin job. Also, partitioners cannot be used while writing data because their implementation is tied to Avro format. See [WriterPartitioner.java](https://github.com/apache/incubator-gobblin/blob/master/gobblin-core-base/src/main/java/org/apache/gobblin/writer/partitioner/WriterPartitioner.java). How will the parquet records be partitioned then? Also, if we decide to write files without Partitioner then the issue is that ```writer.builder.class``` must be a subclass of ```PartitionAwareDataWriterBuilder```, otherwise, Gobblin will throw an error. See [docs](https://gobblin.readthedocs.io/en/latest/user-guide/Configuration-Properties-Glossary/#default-value_126).  Following exceptions are occurring:

@tilakpatidar For a partitioned writer, it means records will be further partitioned into folders than otherwise.  A subclass of `PartitionAwareDataWriterBuilder` would work for both partitioned, if `writer.partitioner.class` is specified, and non-partitioned cases.

The error is not an issue about partitioning but "no output file is generated by the writer". Can you check if the writer actually writes any record? You can add print some messages for verification.
